title: For Sale:  Another Reality Check Today
postcontent: OK people, ask whatever you think your item is worth to you. If it's deemed to high/expensive to some, it may not be to others. If somebody pays an astronomical price, IT DOES NOT MEAN THEY CAN NOT LEGALLY OWN/LEGALLY BUY A WEAPON. It more than likely means they have more money than sense and they want it. It's up to the buyer to do THEIR research and decide to pay that price or not. The great thing about America is capitalism. The seller has every right to ask whatever he/she wants. The seller can also ask for a driver's license and/or a valid CCW before they sell. The sad, but true fact is people are selling guns and ammo for stupid prices all over Armslist as well as gun shops and (especially) gun shows too and people are buying, for whatever their own reasons are. The real Bottom Line is somebody will buy it or they won't. If I or anybody else thinks the price is too high, then we will/can move on. It's up to us the buyers to either let the sellers get away with the high prices or be stuck with their toys. Besides, it gives us all a good laugh sometimes...

title: For Sale:  7.62x54R Ammo 180rds Yugo M908 & M30
postcontent: This listing is for 180 rounds of extra clean and sure to fire 7.62x54R. It's all Yugo surplus and there are six 15 round boxes of M908 and six 15 round boxes of M30. The M908 started as Russian wartime ammunition that was acquired by Yugoslavia. They completely remanufactured it using new sealed primers and powder. The bullets are 147 grain FMJ that attract a magnet so they are probably steel core. The M30 is more recent and it's loaded in beautiful brass cases with a heavy 182 grain lead core bullet. This Yugo ammo is some of the finest surplus out there and prices are going up. Importation of most all surplus has ground to a halt and it's unlikely that large quantities will be coming again like they have in the past. $108 picked up in the Brandon area. Buyer must be at least 18 years old.
